registration:
Online Registration: Registration is available at www.bikereg.com until 11:00 p.m. on Wednesday, August 26th. There will be a $5 late fee added to all entry fees starting on August 1st.  There is a multiple race discount for Sundays criterium.  See packet pick-up information below.
On-site registration:  Registration will be open for the road race from 4:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. on Thursday and from 2:00 p.m. to 10 p.m. on Friday in the Multi-Purpose Events Center (MPEC) located at 1000 Fifth St., Wichita Falls, TX 76301. There will be a $5 late fee added to all entry fees at on-site registration. Criterium registration closes 30 minutes prior to each race start also at the MPEC.

SFA Mountain Bike Classic
description: Saturday STXC and DS at Pioneer Park in Nacogdoches Texas. First event will start at 10am and should conclude by 6pm Sunday XC at Kit McConnaco Park in Lufkin, TX. First wave will go off at 9am second wave will go off around 11am.
course: STXC course will feature one large hill with an accent and decent with open field riding between.
registration: Registration on site from 2 hours before the event til 15 mins before event starts.
directions: To XC: Drive south from Nacogdoches on Hwy 59 and merge south on Hwy 69 north of Lufkin. Exit on first road after bridge over railroad tracks following the signs to the park. Continue to the park and enter, parking in the open field next to the start finish area.

Sun and Ski Sports Presents the Rocky Hill Roundup
description: Season finale of the TMBRA Fall Cup.
course: We will be using the full 21 mile loop for all classes/categories except for 10 and unders, 12 and unders who will race on a 4-6 mile loop.
registration: Register online with BikeReg.com or mail in form available at TMBRA.org. Onsite registration will be available on Saturday the 7th from 1-6 PM and from 7-8:30 AM on raceday.
notes: Rocky Hill Ranch is open year round for riding, race course will be marked by the weekend prior to the race. Saloon is now open for food and drinks. Primitive camping available on site. Pre-entry fee is $30 for adults, $15 for Juniors 13-18, $10 for Juniors 12 and under. Onsite is $5 more for adults.Day use fee of $5 per person per day is collected by the ranch at the gate.
directions: Rocky Hill Ranch is in Smithville Texas, on FM 153 just north of State Hwy 71.
